Load packages and functions

library(tidyverse)
library(data.table)
library(quantreg)
require(pbkrtest)
require(car)
require(heplots)

#Standardize function
standard <- function(x) (x - mean(x, na.rm=T)) / (2*sd(x, na.rm=T))



Set directories and load data

data.dir = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Publication_material/24) Frost risk/R_data/GFBi_tables_for_random_forest/LeafoutSD_tables"
knitr::opts_knit$set(root.dir = data.dir)
output.dir   = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Publication_material/24) Frost risk/R_output"
corrplot.dir = "/Users/consti/Desktop/PhD/Publication_material/24) Frost risk/R_data/CorrplotData"
GFBIclean    = list.files(path=data.dir, pattern = "*.csv") %>% map_df(~fread(., stringsAsFactors = FALSE))



Linear models

########################################################
#Loop to get standardized coefficients from linear model
########################################################

#define explanatory variables
topVariablesVector <- c("sqrt(Q95_DegreeZeroToFrostZero)",
                        "wc2.0_bio_2.5m_01","wc2.0_bio_2.5m_02", "wc2.0_bio_2.5m_07",
                        "wc2.0_bio_2.5m_12","log(wc2.0_bio_2.5m_15)",
                        "sunrad_ave", "sqrt(topo_elevation)", "sqrt(Distance_to_Sea)", "sin(pi*x/180)")

#define biomes
biomes      = unique(GFBIclean$WWF_Biomes_HalfDegree)

#create data frame
lmDataFrame = data.frame(VariableNames = topVariablesVector)

for (biome in biomes){
  tab.sub        <- GFBIclean[GFBIclean$WWF_Biomes_HalfDegree==biome,]
  coeffVect      <- vector()
  for (var in topVariablesVector)
  {
    # create formula
    Formula     <- as.formula(paste("standard(MeanLeafoutSD) ~ standard(",var,")", sep=""))
    # train single linear model for the top ten variables
    coeffSingle <- summary(lm(Formula, data = tab.sub))$coefficients[2]
    # append this to the vector
    coeffVect   <- append(coeffVect,coeffSingle)
  }
  # cbind the name and r square into a data frame
  lmDataFrame <- data.frame(lmDataFrame, coeffVect)
}

colnames(lmDataFrame) <- c("Variables", biomes)

write.table(lmDataFrame, file=paste(corrplot.dir, "CorrplotLeafoutSD.csv", sep="/"), 
            col.names=TRUE, row.names=FALSE, quote=FALSE, sep=",")



Fig. 4d: Quantile regression

# keep only temperate broadleaf forests
GFBIclean = GFBIclean[GFBIclean$WWF_Biomes_HalfDegree %in% c("4"),]

#how many pixels have information?
paste(nrow(GFBIclean), "pixels at 0.5 degree resolution")
## [1] "1868 pixels at 0.5 degree resolution"
#get R2 for effect of LSF on leafout dates
model <- lm(MeanLeafoutSD ~ sqrt(Q95_DegreeZeroToFrostZero), data=GFBIclean)
paste("R2 =", round(summary(lm(model))$r.squared,2))
## [1] "R2 = 0.29"
#########################
#Quantile regression plot
#########################

#define polygons
positions <- data.frame(
  x = c(8,8,35,35),
  y = c(8.47,11.34,7.92,7.44))

QuantileRegPlot = ggplot(GFBIclean, aes(x=sqrt(Q95_DegreeZeroToFrostZero), y=MeanLeafoutSD)) +
  labs(x = "LSF", y = "Interannual Leaf-out variation (SD day-of-year)") +
  geom_polygon(data=positions, aes(x = x, y = y), fill="lightblue") +
  geom_point(size=0.1, color="grey50") +
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(11,31), ylim=c(7.5,11)) +
  geom_quantile(quantiles=c(0.05,0.50,0.95), formula=y ~ x, colour="black") +
  scale_fill_gradientn(colours = rev(terrain.colors(10)),
                       limits=c(0, 8),
                       breaks=c(10,100,200))+
  theme(legend.position= c(0.1, 1.8),
        legend.background = element_rect(fill=NA, 
                                         size=0.5, linetype="solid"),
        axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
        panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        panel.background = element_rect(fill = 'white', colour = 'black')
  )

pdf(paste(output.dir, "Figure4d_quantile_reg_leafoutSD.pdf", sep="/"), width=4, height=4)
QuantileRegPlot
dev.off()
